# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/README.md#shared-version-file
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're building a library, you should not check in Pipfile.lock.
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock should be gitignored when writing a library, but checked in for apps.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock should be gitignored when writing a library, but checked in for apps.
#.pdm.toml
#.pdm-plugins/
#   pdm.lock

